    "actions_taken": [
      "Temperature Safety Element (TSE) Zone 1 initiated Emergency Shutdown (ESD)",
      "Control Room Operator activated well bay deluge system",
      "3-man fire team extinguished fire using two fire hoses with AFFF, fire monitor cannon, and 150# wheel unit",
      "Personnel mustered at Lifeboat #2 with Personal Floatation Devices",
      "Flow assurance chemicals pumped and pressure bled from subsea flow lines",
      "Offshore Installation Manager notified LLOG office, BSEE, and USCG",
      "Platform photographed for damage assessment",
      "Area cleaned on 15 July 2019"
    ],
    "summary": "On 14 July 2019 at 21:50, a fire occurred on LLOG's MC 547 A platform when a 1/2\" isolation valve on Pipeline Pump A's discharge piping developed a crack. Hydrocarbons sprayed onto the hot turbo exhaust system and ignited. The TSE activated the ESD system, all production shut in, and firewater pumps activated. A 3-man fire team extinguished the fire in 16 minutes. No injuries occurred, but pollution was detected on deck and structural supports. The root cause was improper installation of the isolation valve without adequate support, causing fatigue damage from high vibration service.",
    "recommendations": [
      "BSEE New Orleans District made no recommendations to the Office of Incident Investigation"
    ],
